frameDefinitions: These are words relating to emptying containers and clearing areas of some substance or items.
An Developer develops a Product, in some cases for a Company.    '' 'The development of a profitable product will be necessary for the company to stay afloat.
An Item is in a state of dryness.
In this frame, the Patient, an inorganic item, undergoes a chemical process caused by another entity, which renders it less useful, desirable or stable.
An Agent causes a Patient to be wet with a Liquid.
frameExamples: The players <t>emptied</t> the bucket over his head.
The <t>development</t> of a profitable product will be necessary for the company to stay afloat. INI
The metal was <t>corroded</t> by the water.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Agent</fen> is the entity that does the emptying.
The <fen>Theme</fen>, when overtly expressed, invariably occurs in a PP Complement headed by 'of'.
The <fen>Source</fen> is the region or container which is emptied of something.  In this frame, the <fen>Source</fen> occurs as an NP Object.
The <fen>Cause</fen> is the non-sentient force which instigates the emptying.
The time at which the emptying takes place.
The location where the emptying takes place.
The person who develops the <fen>Product</fen>.
The entity which is developed by the <fen>Developer</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Product</fen> is developed by the <fen>Developer</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Product</fen> is developed by the <fen>Developer</fen>.
The <fen>Item</fen> exists in a state of dryness.
The <fen>Patient</fen>  is corroded by the <fen>Cause</fen>.
<fen>Cause</fen> identifies an animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that corrodes the <fen>Patient</fen>. Volitionality is not a necessary characteristic of <fen>Cause</fen>.
The individual that corrodes the <fen>Patient</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Cause</fen> corrodes the <fen>Patient</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Cause</fen> corrodes the <fen>Patient</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is a volitional animate being who causes the <fen>Patient</fen> to become wet.
The <fen>Liquid</fen> is a fluid or gas that permeates or covers the <fen>Patient</fen>.  It most frequently occurs in a PP Complement headed by with.
The <fen>Patient</fen> takes up the <fen>Liquid</fen> through its pores or has the <fen>Liquid</fen> covering its surface.
An animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that produces the state of wetness.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> wets the <fen>Patient</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Agent</fen> wets the <fen>Patient</fen>.
listRoleExamples: <fex>A basic washing</fex> can degrease your workclothes.
The prisoners were deloused <fex>in June and August</fex>.
<fex>Elsa</fex> developed a new line of facial products.
The development of unique, high-quality writing instruments <fex>in the late 1990s</fex> saved the company from going bankrupt.
Gabriela developed her new line of fashion <fex>in Milan</fex>.
<fex>The metal</fex> was corroded by the water.
<fex>Hannah</fex> drenched the cat with anti-flea ointment.
